'''Berend "Bert" Romp''' (4 November 1958 – 4 October 2018) was a Dutch [[equestrianism|equestrian]] and Olympic champion in the sport. He won a gold medal in [[show jumping]] with the Dutch team at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]].<ref name=sports-ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ro/bert-romp-1.html |title=Bert Romp |publisher=Sports Reference LLC |work=SR/Olympic Sports |accessdate=28 December 2008}}</ref>

Romp died on 4 October 2018, a month before his 60th birthday, after a horse kicked him.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rtvnoord.nl/nieuws/199664/Voormalig-springruiter-Bert-Romp-overleden-na-trap-van-paard|title=Voormalig springruiter Bert Romp overleden na trap van paard|work=RTV Noord|access-date=4 October 2018|language=nl-NL}}</ref>

