'''''Pycnoporidium''''' is thought to be a [[genus]] of [[Red algae|red]] or [[Green algae|green alga]]; one species has been synonymized with the [[brachiopod]] ''[[Gosaukammerella]]'', leaving the interpretation of the other species uncertain.<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Senowbari-Daryan | first1 = B. | last2 = Flügel | first2 = E. | title = A ‘Problematic fossil’ revealed:Pycnoporidium ? Eomesozoicum Flügel, 1972 (Late Triassic, Tethys)—not an enigmatic alga but a strophomenid brachiopod (Gosaukammerella n.g.) | journal = Facies | volume = 34 | pages = 83 | year = 1996 | doi = 10.1007/BF02546158}}</ref>

